A Port Elizabeth man has been arrested after police found a modified hunting rifle hidden behind his fridge. Police spokesman Constable Mncedi Mbombo said police raided the man s house at about 11.40pm on Monday after receiving a tip-off about a stolen firearm stashed inside the Luzipho Street house in NU10 Motherwell. Police went to search the house and they found a hunting rifle hidden behind the fridge he said.The hunting rifle barrel had been sawn off and a scope was fitted to the top.Mbombo said police were trying to establish who the gun belonged to.The 20-year-old suspect is expected to appear in the Motherwell Magistrate s Court on Wednesday.